                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7370/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Norwegian Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Norway</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: It is with the deepest sorow that I have the
                    honor to inform your, excellency that I have received a cablegram from the
                    foreign office at Christiania advising me that my beloved chief, Mr. Hauge, died
                    from heart disease this afternoon.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O. Skybak.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
